83rd OREGON LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY--2026 Regular Session
Senate Bill 1546
Printed pursuant to Senate Interim Rule 213.28 by order of the President of the Senate in conformance with pre-
session filing rules, indicating neither advocacy nor opposition on the part of the President (at the request
of Senate Interim Committee on Early Childhood and Behavioral Health)
SUMMARY
The following summary is not prepared by the sponsors of the measure and is not a part of the body thereof subject
to consideration by the Legislative Assembly. It is an editor’s brief statement of the essential features of the
measure as introduced. The statement includes a measure digest written in compliance with applicable readability
standards.
Digest: Tells those who make AI software to tell users that the users are talking to software,
not a human. Tells them they must try to prevent users from getting output that causes suicidal
feelings or thoughts. (Flesch Readability Score: 71.0).
Requires operators of artificial intelligence companions and artificial intelligence platforms to
provide notice to users that the users are interacting with artificial output. Requires the operators
to have in place a protocol for detecting suicidal ideation or intent or self-harm ideation or intent
and to prevent output that could cause such ideation or intent in users. Specifies minimum contents
of the protocol. Requires an operator to make certain statements and disclosures if the operator has
reason to believe that a user that interacts with the operator’s artificial intelligence companion or
artificial intelligence platform is a minor and prohibits the operator from causing the artificial in-
telligence companion to perform certain actions. Requires an operator to report each year to the
Oregon Health Authority concerning incidents in which the operator referred a user to resources
to prevent suicidal ideation, suicide or self-harm.
Allows a user that suffers ascertainable harm to bring an action for damages and injunctive
relief.
1 A BILL FOR AN ACT
2 Relating to artificial intelligence companions.
3 Be It Enacted by the People of the State of Oregon:
4 SECTION 1. (1) As used in this section:
5 (a)(A) “Artificial intelligence companion” means software or a combination of software
6 and hardware that can infer from received natural language input how to generate outputs
7 that can perform one or more of the following actions:
8 (i) Mimic written or spoken natural language or social interaction that is adaptive,
9 anthropomorphic and capable of meeting some users’ social needs;
10 (ii) Use information from a record of previous interactions with the user to engage in
11 dialogues that give the appearance of a continuity of interaction between the user and the
12 artificial intelligence companion or that can mimic some features of a social relationship
13 between the user and the artificial intelligence companion;
14 (iii) Adapt to new circumstances or new input while maintaining a continuity of
15 anthropomorphic features that mimic a human personality; or
16 (iv) Generate output that can affect, control or influence a natural person’s behavior or
17 a physical or virtual environment.
18 (B) “Artificial intelligence companion” does not include:
19 (i) Software that operates solely for the purpose of customer service, business oper-
20 ations, productivity, information analysis, internal research or technical assistance, regard-
21 less of the software’s capability to use natural language inputs and generate natural
22 language outputs;
NOTE: Matter in boldfaced type in an amended section is new; matter [italic and bracketed] is existing law to be omitted.
New sections are in boldfaced type.
